{"id":"moza","term":"Moza","source":"Easton's Bible Dictionary (M.G. Easton, 1897)","html":"<p>A going forth. (1.) One of the sons of Caleb (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"1 Chronicles 2:46\">1 Chr. 2:46</a>).</p>\n<p>(2.) The son of Zimri, of the posterity of Saul (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"1 Chronicles 8:36\">1 Chr. 8:36</a>, <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Genesis 2:6\">37</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Genesis 10:13\">9:42</a>, <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Genesis 10:14\">43</a>).</p>\n\u0000","refs":["1 Chronicles 2:46","1 Chronicles 8:36","Genesis 2:6","Genesis 10:13","Genesis 10:14"]}